team19.weatherapp

Class CurrentWeather

  • java.lang.Object
    • team19.weatherapp.CurrentWeather

  • public class CurrentWeather
extends java.lang.Object
    The CurrrentWeather class holds all of the current weather data for the specified city. When the json is parsed, it is passed into the CurrentWeather constructor, which retrieves the data from the JSONObject and saves it into multiple variables. Once saved, a user can easy access any of these variables by referencing them through the city object.
    Author:
    Scott Mackie

    • Constructor Detail

      • CurrentWeather

        public CurrentWeather(org.json.JSONObject j,
                      char tempUnits,
                      char windUnits)
               throws org.json.JSONException
        The CurrentWeather constructor retrieves the JSONObject data, and saves the data into variable fields. The data is saved in the format specified by tempUnits and windUnits.
        Parameters:
        j - This is the JSONObject that the city data is retrieved from
        tempUnits - The temperature units shows which units the temperature data should be stored in
        windUnits - The wind units show which units the wind data should be stored in
        Throws:
        org.json.JSONException - Throws a JSONExcpetion, required for JSONObjects
